{{Quote|Because we were willing to die for our cause, we became the Death Watch, led by the Secret Mandalores. To ensure we would be led by the most powerful, we decreed that any warrior could challenge the Secret Mandalore for leadership of Death Watch.|[[Tor Vizsla]]|<ref name="TBHC" />}}
The title of '''Secret Mandalore''' was one assumed by the leader of the radical [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] splinter group known as the [[Death Watch/Legends|Death Watch]]. These individuals held the belief that they were the true claimants to the traditional role of [[Mandalore (title)/Legends|''Mand'alor'']], leader of the Mandalorian people and clans. 

They stood in opposition to the "[[Jaster Mereel|True Mandalore]]," chosen by the members of the mainstream Mandalorian warrior clans who sided with the [[True Mandalorians|True Mandalorian]] faction. In addition, they stood against the Mandalorians they considered 'faithless', namely the [[New Mandalorians/Legends|New Mandalorian]] people who were ruled by those that the movement came to dub as "[[Anti-Mandalore|Anti-Mandalores]]". 

==Notable Secret Mandalores==
===Pre Vizsla===
{{Main|Pre Vizsla/Legends}}
[[File:PreVizslaHS-AFIN.png|thumb|right|175px|Pre Vizsla]]
{{Quote|People of Mandalore, I am Pre Vizsla of Clan Vizsla. Death Watch is here to save you from these intergalactic gangsters that threaten our great city. This is a war, and we will ''win!'' Join me, and let us defend Mandalore against the criminals. We need ''action'', not pacifism!|Pre Vizsla|<ref name="SoR">{{TCW|Shades of Reason}}</ref>}}
At the start of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[Pre Vizsla/Legends|Pre Vizsla]] had stood publicly as the [[Governor/Legends|governor]] of [[Concordia/Legends|Concordia]],<ref name="TMP">{{TCW|The Mandalore Plot}}</ref> one of [[Mandalore/Legends|Mandalore's]] two [[Moon/Legends|moons]],<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> but in secret, he was the latest leader of the radical Mandalorian splinter group known as Death Watch. Vizsla despised the pacifistic [[New Mandalorians/Legends|New Mandalorians]] and their [[Anti-Mandalore|leader]], [[Duchess/Legends|Duchess]] [[Satine Kryze/Legends|Satine Kryze]], believing the Mandalorians would be better off reclaiming their ancient role as [[Mandalorian Crusaders|conquering warriors]]. To this end, Vizsla aligned Death Watch with the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]] during the [[Cloning/Legends|Clone]] Wars, promising his support to the cause if the Confederacy's leader, [[Count/Legends|Count]] [[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]], aided him in deposing Kryze.<ref name="TMP" /> Despite their efforts to manipulate the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] into moving against Mandalore, believing an armed Republic [[Mandalore Defense Resolution/Legends|occupation]] would trigger the New Mandalorian populous to violently rebel and rally to Death Watch, Kryze was able to stem the Republic's occupation plans by speaking out before the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], and Vizsla's plans were dashed.<ref name="DoM">{{TCW|Duchess of Mandalore}}</ref> Death Watch was eventually exiled from the [[Mandalore system/Legends|Mandalore system]],<ref name="Zanbar">{{SWE|locations|zanbar|Zanbar}}</ref> and Pre Vizsla had a falling out with Dooku that left his face scarred and his hatred for the Confederate leader immense.<ref name="AFiN">{{TCW|A Friend in Need}}</ref> Vizsla led the now nomadic Death Watch<ref name="Zanbar" /> across [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]], [[Carlac Death Watch camp/Legends|settling]] on the [[Water/Legends|snowy]] world of [[Carlac/Legends|Carlac]],<ref name="AFiN" /> before moving on to the swamp-covered moon of [[Zanbar/Legends|Zanbar]].<ref name="Zanbar" />

During one of Death Watch's travels, Vizsla came across the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth Maul]], and through the [[Zabrak/Legends|Zabrak]] [[Sith/Legends|Sith]], found a new path to overturning the New Mandalorians' pacifism. Vizsla formed an alliance with Maul, and together they established a criminal contingent known as the [[Shadow Collective/Legends|Shadow Collective]] by recruiting elements of [[Black Sun/Legends|Black Sun]], the [[Spice/Legends|spice]]-[[Drug dealer|dealing]] [[Pyke Syndicate/Legends|Pyke Syndicate]], and the foot soldiers of the [[Hutt Cartel/Legends|Hutt Cartels]]. With their [[Army/Legends|army]] of criminals, Vizsla and Maul put a plan for [[Takeover of Mandalore/Legends|overthrowing]] the New Mandalorian [[Ruling Council (New Mandalorians)/Legends|government]] into action: the Collective's [[Gangster/Legends|gangsters]] would assault the New Mandalorian [[Capital/Legends|capital]] [[City/Legends|city]] of [[Sundari/Legends|Sundari]] and create chaos, making Duchess Kryze appear weak in the [[Eye/Legends|eyes]] of her people, only for Death Watch to arrive and rescue the New Mandalorian citizenry from their attackers and win public favor. The plan went as intended, with the New [[Mandalorian Guard/Legends|Mandalorian police]] unable to combat the numbers and firepower of the offworld criminals; the New Mandalorian people sought the aid of an administration that could do nothing to protect them, and it was only when Death Watch took to combating the criminals overtaking Sundari that order was restored. With the backing of the people, Pre Vizsla stormed the [[Sundari Royal Palace/Legends|Sundari Royal Palace]] and had Kryze [[Prisoner/Legends|arrested]].<ref name="ShadowConspiracy">''[[The Clone Wars: Darth Maul: Shadow Conspiracy]]''</ref> The Secret Mandalore of Death Watch<ref name="TBHC" /> took his place as the new leader of the New Mandalorians. Vizsla's [[Time/Legends|time]] as ''Mand'alor'' of the New Mandalorians was short-lived, however, for with his goals met, he turned upon his Sith ally and tried to have [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Maul [[Prison/Legends|incarcerated]]. Maul escaped his confines and challenged Vizsla to a fight to the death for leadership. Though Vizsla fought fiercely,<ref name="ShadowConspiracy" /> making use of the full arsenal his [[Mandalorian armor/Legends|Mandalorian armor]] made available to him,<ref name="SoR" /> he was defeated and killed by Maul, who proclaimed himself to be the new leader of Death Watch<ref name="ShadowConspiracy" /> and Secret Mandalore.<ref name="TBHC" />

===Darth Maul===
{{Main|Darth Maul/Legends}}
[[File:DarthMaul-ChroniclesPrequels.jpg|thumb|right|175px|Darth Maul]]
{{Quote|I claim this sword, and my rightful place as leader of Death Watch!|Darth Maul, taking possession of the Darksaber|<ref name="SoR" />}}
From a young age, the [[Dathomir/Legends|Dathomir]]-native named Maul was raised and trained as a Sith by the [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Darth Sidious]].<ref name="Plagueis">[[Darth Plagueis (novel)|''Darth Plagueis'']]</ref> Becoming Sidious' [[Sith apprentice/Legends|Sith apprentice]] and earning the title of Darth upon his ascendance to Sith [[Lord/Legends|Lord]], Maul became a fearsome force in his [[Sith Master/Legends|master's]] [[Grand Plan/Legends|plan]] to conquer the galaxy. However, his time under Sidious was cut short when, in [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]], Maul was grievously wounded by the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] while on [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]]. Cut in half at the waist,<ref name="WoDM">''[[The Wrath of Darth Maul]]''</ref> it was only Maul's hatred and the power of the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]] that kept him alive, languishing for years in [[Darth Maul's lair/Legends|squalor]] on a garbage-covered [[Lotho Minor/Legends|world]] where his body had ended up until he was found, half insane, by his estranged brother [[Savage Opress/Legends|Savage Opress]]. Opress took Maul back to Dathomir, where his mind was restored and his body was rebuilt with [[Cybernetics/Legends|cybernetics]] by the [[Nightsisters/Legends|Nightsister]] [[Mother (title)/Legends|Mother]] [[Talzin/Legends|Talzin]]. Possessed of his faculties once more, Maul set out to exact revenge upon Kenobi,<ref name="Revenge">{{TCW|Revenge (episode)}}</ref> taking Opress as his own Sith apprentice.<ref name="ShadowConspiracy" />

Maul's pursuit of vengeance eventually led him into an alliance with the radical Mandalorian Death Watch and their leader, Pre Vizsla. Seeing their combat prowess and efficiency as useful, the Sith agreed to help Vizsla topple the regime of the pacifist New Mandalorians. Together they assembled a collective of criminals comprised of gangsters from Black Sun, the [[Pyke/Legends|Pyke]] Syndicate, and the Hutt [[Kajidic/Legends|kajidics]], only to set them lose on the New Mandalorian capital of Sundari to spread fear and chaos in order to undermine the pacifist administration. With the people in a panic, Death Watch was sent in to stop the criminals, putting on a show for the populace that won the public's favor. Disgraced, the New Mandalorian leader Satine Kryze was deposed and Pre Vizsla took her place, only to immediately turn upon Maul and his apprentice. Unbeknownst to the Death Watch leader, Maul had anticipated his betrayal: the Sith Lord challenged Vizsla to a duel for leadership, killing him and proclaiming himself<ref name="ShadowConspiracy" /> to be the new Secret Mandalore<ref name="TBHC" /> in charge of Death Watch. Maul's leadership was challenged by elements of the Death Watch loyal to Vizsla's [[Lieutenant/Legends|lieutenant]], [[Bo-Katan Kryze/Legends|Bo-Katan Kryze]], who refused to follow a non-Mandalorian like Maul, instead breaking away from those who swore fealty to the Sith Lord. Maul reinstated the former Prime [[Minister]] Almec to serve as a puppet ruler of the New Mandalorians, so that he could affect control over both factions while remaining unseen by the galaxy at large. Despite this, Maul's former master, Darth Sidious, was able to track his one-time apprentice to the planet Mandalore, where he [[Battle of Mandalore/Legends|engaged]] Maul and Savage Opress in a lightsaber battle<ref name="ShadowConspiracy" /> that ended with Opress's demise and a beaten Maul brought to heel by the Dark Lord of the Sith for his own purposes.<ref name="Lawless">{{TCW|The Lawless}}</ref>

===Lorka Gedyc===
{{Main|Lorka Gedyc}}
{{Quote|We conquered whole star systems. We had an empire. When cities heard our armies were coming, populations fled before a shot was fired. Now we cling to a pathetic sector of dirtball planets, we scramble for the crumbs that the cowardly ''aruetiise'' throw when they want us to fight for them, and they use us as a breeding stock for their clone armies. The ''aruetiise'' will always treat us like an animal species to be used for their convenience until we stand up for ourselves again.|Lorka Gedyc|<ref name="ImpCom501st">''[[Imperial Commando: 501st]]''</ref>}}
After Death Watch fractured and turned upon itself following Maul's ascension to leadership,<ref name="Lawless" /> Lorka Gedyc formed a new iteration of Death Watch, assuming leadership over the group by [[19 BBY]]. Gedyc thought highly of the [[Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders/Legends|Mandalorians]] of old, who had [[Mandalorian Wars|forged]] an empire<ref name="ImpCom501st" /> that spanned across vast swaths of the galaxy.<ref name="TEA" /> The now diminished state of the [[Mandalore sector/Legends|Mandalore sector]] was abhorrent to Gedyc, and the Death Watch leader felt that the Mandalorians' penchant for mercenary and bounty hunting work was tantamount to scrambling for crumbs. Following the Republic's [[Declaration of a New Order|reorganization]] into the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], Lorka Gedyc saw an opportunity to restore the glory and power Death Watch believed the Mandalorians had lost. Gedyc allied Death Watch with the new Empire, and directed Death Watch members [[Dred Priest]] and [[Isabet Reau]] to assist the Imperials in establishing their [[Garrison/Legends|garrison]] on Mandalore, just outside the planetary [[Capital/Legends|capital]] city of [[Keldabe/Legends|Keldabe]]<ref name="ImpCom501st" /> in the "[[City of Bone]]."<ref name="TEA" /> Priest thought highly of Gedyc and the Death Watch leader's plans, though he was killed for his ties to the radical sect by fellow Mandalorian [[Mij Gilamar]],<ref name="TEA" /> and the Empire ultimately moved to enslave Mandalore and its people.<ref name="TEA" />

==Behind the scenes==
Death Watch and its leader were first introduced to the ''[[Star Wars]]'' universe with the release of the [[Star Wars: Jango Fett: Open Seasons|''Jango Fett: Open Seasons'']] series, written by [[W. Haden Blackman|Haden Blackman]] and published in [[2002]].<ref name="OpenSeasons">''[[Star Wars: Jango Fett: Open Seasons]]''</ref> The [[Republic Commando|''Republic'' and ''Imperial Commando'' series]] of novels by [[Author/Legends|author]] [[Karen Traviss]],<ref name="ImpCom501st" /> as well as the ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'' television series also introduced other leaders of Death Watch during and after the Clone Wars,<ref name="ShadowConspiracy" /> but it was only with the [[2013]] release of [[The Bounty Hunter Code: From the Files of Boba Fett|''The Bounty Hunter Code'']] reference book by [[Jason Fry]], [[Daniel Wallace]], and [[Ryder Windham]], that the Death Watch leader was given the proper title of Secret Mandalore.<ref name="TBHC" />

